{
  "texts": [
    "As discussed in the previous section, the contribution of most papers focused on these embedding functions.",
    "For example, the work in Fouladvand et al. (2021) uses the sum of two LSTM network outputs, which have the diagnosis and medication longitudinal data as input.",
    "These inputs are also summed to the months when they were assessed.",
    "The work in Boursalie et al. (2021) first calculates the elapsed time between two visits (longitudinal unit) and concatenates this value to the diagnosis and medication codes.",
    "The final embedding is summed to the positional encoding."
  ]
}